		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top" id="forumSubject">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Wed, Feb 6th 7:28 AM2002 </span><span class="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=14&mid=101282478153368&num=1&post=1&replyto=101299477261096"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a> | <a class="sm" href="/db/journal2.html?user=49677"><img border="0" src="/shared/user_journal.gif" border="0" height="12" width="17" /> User's Journal</a>   <a name=101299477261096></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=49677"><span id=Guru>alaaraaf the Puissant</span></a><b><span id=Guru><br>Guru</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />179 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=alaaraaf&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Hey.<br /><br />Most of what I needed to know, I have figured out for myself.&nbsp;&nbsp;So, I'll share, in case anyone else is interested...<br /><br /><li><b>Faction in Paineel:</b><br />There seems to be only one faction for the residents of Paineel.  This, is of course, the <b>Heretic</b> faction.  This does <b>not</b> however, cover every NPC to be found in the city.<br />There are several NPCs who have remained unaffected by my faction manipulation.  One of these, <a href="HTTP://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=5194" target="akztarg">Duriek Bloodpool</a> is involved in the Innoruuk's curse quest and is apparently on the True Spirit faction.  I don't nkow about the others.  However, as an Iksar they are dubious to me.  This being the case, I am inclined tothink that probably no-one starts KoS to these NPCs.<br />Raising Heretic faction is blissfully simple.  Wander into the Warrens and kill everything that breathes.  I initially went from scowling to aimiable on about eight hundred kobolds.  <i>(I'm back at scowling after killing Heretics for Erudin factions, but since killing kobolds doesn't lower Erudin factions, I can fix that after I fix my other factions.)</i><br />Heretic faction is very easy to raise in the Warrens.  I acheived aimiable the first time on approximately eight hundred kills in the Warrens.  As a counterpoint, this same number of kills only got me to dubious, with the High Guard of Erudin, who are also improved by killing Kobolds.<br /><br /><li><b>Erudin factions:</b><br />This is a bit more tricky...<br />Every guild in Erudin seems to have it's own faction!  In addition to this, there are the High Guard, who also have their own faction and <b>maybe</b> the traders in the city.  <i>(I'm not entirely sure about that bit yet!)</i><br /><b>High Guard of Erudin:</b> <br />These are the guards.  As stated above, you can improve faction with these guys, by killing in the Warrens.  However, be aware that you will need to kill far more kobolds to be accepted by these guys, than you will to be accepted by the Heretics.  (This isn't such a bad thing.  I've been from Scowling, to aimiable and back to scowling with the Heretics.  By the time I've finished and been back in the Warrens for more Paineel faction, I should be aimiable, or so with both the High Guard and the Heretics!  *Grin*)<br /><i>Update:  1174 kobolds has raised me to aimiable with the High Guard.</i><br />Raising other factions seems to be impossible without lowering Heretic faction.  I have been killing <a href="HTTP://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=6634" target="akztarg">Azzar Habbib</a> <i>(Azzar is by no means level fifty!!!  He is green at level forty-nine and has maybe fifteen hundred hit points.)</i> and <a href="HTTP://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=4888" target="akztarg">Noclin Saah</a> in the Paineel newbie area, along with <a href="HTTP://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=3396" target="akztarg">Elial Brook in Paineel</a>.  Each kill gives positive faction hits to four factions in Erudin, a negative faction hit to the Heretics, but no hit on the High Guard.<br /><b>DeepWater knights:</b><br />Approximately ninety Heretic kills, raised me to dubious, with <a href="HTTP://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=497" target="akztarg">Tiam Khonsir</a>, who issues the <a href="HTTP://www.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=1243" target="akztarg">kobold molar</a> quests.  Tiam is on the DeepWater knights faction, which represents the paladins of Prexus.  Approximately 100 molars has raised me to aimiable with this faction.  <i>(These molars are a pain to collect.  They're pretty uncommon.  Out of 213 kobolds killed in my last session in the Warrens, I found only 64 molars.  (That's maybe not too horrendous.  It felt like I killed more though!  *Shrug*))</i><br />This raises faction with both the DeepWater knights and the High Council of Erudin.  (I don't have a clue, who the High Council are.  But, they shouldnt't wanna kill me now, so that's ok!  *Grin*)<br /><b>Gate Callers:</b><br />The Gate Callers are the magicians of Erudin.  The guild master of this guild, <a href="HTTP://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=610" target="akztarg">Markus Jaevins</a>, desires the remains of a purged Heretic.  These are bones, which are dropped by Elial Brook, in Toxxulia forest.  <i>(These things look like bone chips and are stackable, but are named 'bones'.)</i>  I had about forty bones and handed these in, which raised me to Warmly, with the magicians.  <i>(I could've sworn I had another stack, but I can't find them.  I need to have a look in the bank!)</i><br /><br />This is as far as I have gotten so far.<br /><li>Aimiable with the DeepWater knights.<br /><li>Aimiable with the High Guard of Erudin.<br /><li>Warmly with the Gate Callers.<br /><br />I am dubious, or apprehensive to most other NPCs in Erudin.  Indifferent, to what I am guessing is the, vendors' faction and <b>still</b> scowling with maybe half a dozen or so NPCs I have found.  Most notably the bankers (???) and a couple of NPCs close to the teleporter to the Erudin Palace area.  <br /><br />Sadly, the bestiary section doesn't contain any information on which factions effect each NPC, so working out how to raise each is a little tricky.  (I have read that giving wood chips to the vendor in the hut closest to the entrance to Erudin in Paineel, will raise the vendors faction.  So, I'll probably try this next.)  Not being able to bank is a pain in the ass!  <br /><br />On the upside, I have the faction I needed for the Titan sample quests.  So I can at least pursue these.<br /><br />I will post more, as I find out what works.<br /><br />Hope this helps someone.<br /><br />AlAaraaf.<br /><br /><br /><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Feb  6 17:28:21 2002</em></p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />"Te aurdire no possum. Musa sapienum fixa est in aura."</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td></tr></table>
